ent-STWeaponSniperSVDS = SVDS (Dragunov Sniper Rifle)
    .desc = A modernized folding version of the legendary SVD sniper rifle, chambered in 7.62x54mmR. Features improved ergonomics and comes equipped with a medium-range scope. A favorite among Zone marksmen for its reliability and stopping power.
ent-STWeaponSniperSVDSGrass = SVDS Ghillie Sniper Rifle
    .desc = A carefully modified SVDS with camouflage netting and minor tuning for maximum concealment in the Zone's wilderness. The 7.62x54mmR rounds ensure no mutant walks away from a well-placed shot.
ent-STWeaponSniperSVDSCovenant = Covenant SVDS Sniper Rifle
    .desc = A custom SVDS variant used by Covenant faction snipers. Features unique camouflage and faction markings while retaining all the deadly precision of the original. Chambered in 7.62x54mmR.
ent-STWeaponSniperSVU = SVU Compact Sniper Rifle
    .desc = A bullpup conversion of the SVDS designed for urban operations in the Zone. The shortened barrel reduces range but improves handling in tight spaces, while still delivering 7.62x54mmR stopping power.
ent-STWeaponSniperSVUSeraphim = Seraphim SVU Sniper Rifle
    .desc = An elite SVU variant used by the mysterious Seraphim faction. Features advanced modifications and distinctive white finish, making it both deadly and recognizable in the Zone's harsh environment.
ent-STWeaponRifleSVDSWood = Selfmade chatter
    .desc = A selfmade rifle for an SVD magazine. Oblique, but wildly lethal.

# Zona14: merged content from case-duplicate file to fix Windows case-insensitive checkout collision
ent-STWeaponSniperSVUTop = SVU "Top"
    .desc = The shortened sniper rifle - a self-loading sniper rifle of bullpup layout, developed by TsKIB SOO on the basis of the SVD. Development of a shortened SVD-based sniper rifle for the USSR airborne troops began at TsKIB SOO in 1977. In 1979 demonstration samples of designer L. V. Bondarev's SVU rifle were offered to the airborne forces, but it did not reach production at that time. Serial production of the SVU began in 1991, and the first production rifles entered service with the 106th Guards Airborne Division, where they underwent field trials. The barrel is fitted with a massive masking muzzle device designed by L. V. Bondarev. The suppressor reduces the sound level of the shot by 10-12% compared to the SVD, almost completely eliminates muzzle flash, and disperses the sound of the shot in such a way that determining the shooter's exact position becomes impossible. The furniture is made of polyamide. On this example, the bulk of the body, including the stock, is wrapped in camouflage tape, with additional wrapping on the scope and muzzle device that breaks up the silhouette of the weapon against vegetation.
    .suffix = ST, custom
ent-STWeaponSniperPP2000Pearl = PP-2000
    .desc = A gun made either by a desperate genius or by a schizophrenic. Apparently the barrel was made by welding several identical barrels together... Wait, why does it have a removable drum?! An illegible signature of the maker is scratched into the forend.
